pageContext.claim: “If I showed you a map, much of the map says, it's gone. It's gone from big areas of our country.”
pageContext.analysis: Large portions of the country do have few coronavirus cases, but large portions of the country also have relatively few people. In other words, few cases that does not necessarily mean that they are “corona-free” or doing better than large metropolitan areas. Indeed, when considering total cases per 100,000 people, some of the hardest hit areas are rural.
